pedia.org/resource/Bradley_Braves_men's_basketball\"}, {\"begin\": 514, \"end\": 531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"score\": 0.9999968692872139, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaun Maswanganyi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\"}, {\"begin\": 564, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4909377307104626e-29, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 625, \"end\": 630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999681677, \"rank\": 3.167176844762658e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Furthermore, Simbine will feel a degree of justice and relief after missing out on a medal by 0.01 seconds in the epic 100m final.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All four silver medallists - and every medal winner will pocket some good money.\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 845, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Tatjana Smith claimed gold and silver, racking up big-money upon wrapping up an even bigger career.\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 957, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The South African Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee (Sascoc) announced their financial incentive structure for the athletes and coaches prior to the global showpiece.\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 1134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As reported onThe South African, here are the incentives for track relay athletes.\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1218, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medal: R100 000 per athlete and the coach R100 000Silver medal: R75 000 per athlete and the coach R75 000Bronze medal: R50 000 per athlete and the coach R50 000  Akani Simbine pocketedR75 000afterTeam SAsecured a silver medal in the 4x100m relay in Paris on Friday evening.\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1387, \"end\": 1400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}, {\"begin\": 1474, \"end\": 1479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999681677, \"rank\": 3.167176844762658e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bradley Nkoana, Bayanda Walaza, Shaun Maswanganyi also took homeR75 000.\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1500, \"end\": 1507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Braves_men's_basketball\", \"score\": 0.9934480198883212, \"rank\": 0.003789305311785654, \"text\": \"Bradley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Braves_men's_basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradley_Braves_men's_basketball\"}, {\"begin\": 1532, \"end\": 1549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"score\": 0.9999968692872139, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaun Maswanganyi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simbine was a split second away fromR50 000(a bronze) after an epic photo finish that saw Noah Lyles win a classic 100m that will live long in the memory of athletics fans and sports fans alike.\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1664, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, he missed out on the podium finish and incentive.\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Simbine set a national record after clocking in a national record with a blistering 9.86m in the 100m sprint.\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1954, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Iconic South African swimmer, Tatiana Smith, conquered the world on her route to securing her gold medal in the 100m breaststroke final.\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 2092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1986, \"end\": 1993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Duchess_Tatiana_Nikolaevna_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999993997450457, \"rank\": 5.876948541992948e-07, \"text\": \"Tatiana\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Duchess_Tatiana_Nikolaevna_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Duchess_Tatiana_Nikolaevna_of_Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Furthermore, she clocked in an impressive time of 1:05:28 on route to her first of two medals.\", \"from\": 2094, \"to\": 2188, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally, Smith secured another medal, this time a silver medal, in the 200m breaststroke.\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Therefore, Smith took home a total ofR600 000(R400 000for gold andR200 000for silver).\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What a finish!\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below this article or by emailinginfo@thesouthafrican.comor sending a Whats